WEBVTT

00:06.615 --> 00:07.964
[Gasping]

00:08.051 --> 00:09.226
Allison Devine?

00:09.270 --> 00:10.706
Everybody wanted
to get out of here.

00:10.793 --> 00:12.534
You at least had a shot.

00:12.577 --> 00:13.883
Woman: You need to get
Gertrude's death certificate.

00:13.970 --> 00:15.363
I think I know someone
who can help us with this.

00:15.450 --> 00:16.668
This is someone I know
at City Hall.

00:16.755 --> 00:17.887
They'll get you
whatever you need.

00:17.974 --> 00:19.193
After this, I'm done.

00:19.280 --> 00:20.411
I'm faking
my own death.

00:20.498 --> 00:21.717
My dad has a new girlfriend.

00:21.804 --> 00:23.197
[Man laughs weirdly]

00:23.284 --> 00:24.459
We're going to set up
Pete.

00:24.546 --> 00:26.069
I do not want to sleep
with Diane.

00:26.113 --> 00:27.201
Excuse me?

00:27.288 --> 00:28.550
Him and Kevin
were joking.

00:28.637 --> 00:30.813
To who?To not drinking alone.

00:30.900 --> 00:31.988
[Woman yelps]

00:32.075 --> 00:33.337
Everything's going
to be fine.

00:33.424 --> 00:36.036
It's the security footage
from Vermont, right?

00:37.124 --> 00:39.039
[Mid-tempo music plays]

00:39.126 --> 00:40.562
Ugh.

00:40.649 --> 00:41.954
Hello.

00:42.042 --> 00:43.869
For who?
Huh?

00:43.956 --> 00:45.958
I-I thought you said
"good morning."

00:46.046 --> 00:49.092
[Laughing]
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah!

00:49.136 --> 00:50.833
[Studio audience laughing]

00:50.920 --> 00:52.313
You're too much!

00:52.400 --> 00:55.229
I just came by to bathe
with your father.

00:55.316 --> 01:00.060
You know, two birds,
one stone.

01:00.147 --> 01:01.365
What are the birds?

01:01.452 --> 01:03.759
And what is the stone?!

01:03.802 --> 01:06.196
Ugh.
Better take this out.

01:06.283 --> 01:07.632
It lets me hear,

01:07.676 --> 01:10.766
but it doesn't mix well
with sudsy Pete water.

01:10.809 --> 01:14.117
Yeah. Wouldn't want it to zap
your brain and kill you.

01:14.204 --> 01:17.903
Oh! I know I'd be laughing,
but I can't hear you!

01:17.990 --> 01:18.861
[Chuckles]

01:18.904 --> 01:21.646
[Studio audience laughing]

01:21.690 --> 01:24.432
[Hearing aid plops]

01:24.475 --> 01:26.086
[Exhales deeply]

01:26.173 --> 01:28.653
Ah!
I didn't say that!

01:28.740 --> 01:31.308
That is
so out of context!

01:31.395 --> 01:34.137
And what is that doing
in there?

01:34.181 --> 01:37.053
[Studio audience laughing]

01:39.011 --> 01:40.970
A hit job.What?

01:41.013 --> 01:44.539
I'm just reading the article,
which you stole from me!

01:44.626 --> 01:46.410
There's a whole paragraph
in here

01:46.497 --> 01:48.673
about your high school
swimming career

01:48.760 --> 01:50.501
from like
a thousand years ago!

01:50.588 --> 01:52.634
And a picture!

01:52.721 --> 01:55.985
That space could've been used
for my quips, goofs,

01:56.028 --> 01:57.639
and timeless maxims.

01:57.726 --> 02:00.163
Where are my maxims,
Allison?!

02:00.207 --> 02:02.296
[Studio audience laughing]

02:02.383 --> 02:04.080
"She was poised to have
her own legacy

02:04.167 --> 02:06.996
but chose to end her swimming
career after her junior year."

02:07.039 --> 02:09.303
Ooh.
Allison didn't finish something.

02:09.390 --> 02:11.043
How is that news?

02:11.087 --> 02:13.655
"You can find her working
at the Defto's package store."

02:13.698 --> 02:15.178
A real blow.

02:15.265 --> 02:16.832
What the hell?
I don't even work there anymore.

02:16.919 --> 02:19.400
I mean for me.

02:19.487 --> 02:23.534
But I have figured out a way
to take back my narrative.

02:23.621 --> 02:25.493
The Worcester Wild Dude
has been put in charge

02:25.580 --> 02:28.365
of the city's Fourth of July
fireworks display this year,

02:28.409 --> 02:30.715
and it seems like a surefire way
to bring back

02:30.802 --> 02:34.197
all the deep respect
which I so richly deserve.

02:34.284 --> 02:36.721
I'm gonna reply in a way
that sounds like I'm listening,

02:36.765 --> 02:38.984
but I'm really not.

02:39.071 --> 02:40.160
That's the spirit!

02:40.247 --> 02:42.031
Hey, uh,
Neil's coming over later

02:42.118 --> 02:45.861
to help me sync up explosions
with random Aerosmith songs,

02:45.948 --> 02:47.341
so...

02:49.908 --> 02:52.041
Ah.
A little waxy.

02:52.084 --> 02:54.348
[Studio audience laughing]

02:55.958 --> 02:59.309
[Dog barking,
horn honking in distance]

03:04.923 --> 03:06.708
[Cellphone clicks]

03:06.751 --> 03:09.189
Woman: The caller you've reached
is unavailable.

03:09.276 --> 03:10.799
Hi.
Hi.

03:10.886 --> 03:13.367
Uh, this is, uh,
this is Sam's friend Alli--

03:13.454 --> 03:15.717
Al...ice.
Alice.

03:15.804 --> 03:19.024
Uh, he told me that you could
help me out with some documents

03:19.111 --> 03:21.113
from city hall.

03:21.201 --> 03:24.334
Anyway, let me know
if you can meet up tonight.

03:24.421 --> 03:26.728
Okay. Thank you.
Bye.

03:30.819 --> 03:33.300
[Mid-tempo introduction plays]

03:33.387 --> 03:40.437
♪♪

03:40.481 --> 03:41.612
Oh.

03:41.656 --> 03:43.919
Oh, no, no, no, no.

03:44.006 --> 03:48.750
♪♪

03:48.793 --> 03:50.447
Hm.

03:50.534 --> 03:55.322
♪♪

03:55.409 --> 03:59.021
[Electricity buzzing,
studio audience laughing]

03:59.108 --> 04:02.111
[High-pitched ringing,
laughter continues]

04:05.723 --> 04:08.726
[Birds chirping,
vehicles passing in distance]

04:17.692 --> 04:19.302
Oh.
Hi.

04:19.389 --> 04:20.782
You didn't tell me
you were coming over.

04:20.825 --> 04:21.739
I know.

04:21.826 --> 04:23.132
And you cut your hair.

04:23.175 --> 04:24.481
I had to do something.

04:24.525 --> 04:26.135
It feels like
something's off,

04:26.222 --> 04:28.920
and this seemed like
a dramatic gesture or whatever.

04:29.007 --> 04:29.965
The haircut?

04:30.008 --> 04:31.445
No.
Coming over.

04:33.751 --> 04:36.145
I've barely heard from you
since my birthday.

04:36.232 --> 04:39.844
I'm sorry.
I-I just -- I've been busy.

04:39.888 --> 04:42.369
Since when are you
too busy?

04:42.456 --> 04:45.415
You once texted me
while arresting someone.

04:45.502 --> 04:48.897
It's just...
It's just bad timing.

04:48.984 --> 04:51.291
I'll call you later.
No.

04:52.727 --> 04:53.989
No, you won't.

05:00.517 --> 05:04.173
Is there something,
like, goin' on?

05:04.913 --> 05:07.132
Yeah.

05:07.219 --> 05:10.658
[Siren wailing in distance]

05:17.055 --> 05:20.450
I've been trying to figure out
how to talk to you about this.

05:20.537 --> 05:23.758
I just never
figured it out.

05:25.760 --> 05:27.675
So I didn't talk
at all.

05:29.590 --> 05:31.418
Okay.
Can you...

05:38.250 --> 05:40.252
I'm just gonna say it.

05:40.340 --> 05:41.863
Okay.

05:41.950 --> 05:44.692
And think abot
how you want this to go

05:44.779 --> 05:45.823
before you respond.

05:45.910 --> 05:47.216
Tammy, just say --

05:47.303 --> 05:49.523
Do you want to move in
with me?

05:50.393 --> 05:52.961
I just like having you around.
That's all.

05:56.007 --> 06:00.621
Actually...you might be
the best thing in my life,

06:00.708 --> 06:03.885
and I want to spend
all my time with you.

06:05.060 --> 06:07.367
I think it could be really good
for both of us.

06:14.417 --> 06:16.593
Okay.
You can respond at some point.

06:16.680 --> 06:18.290
Uh...

06:18.378 --> 06:20.597
[Mid-tempo music plays]

06:20.641 --> 06:23.774
Well, um...

06:23.861 --> 06:26.603
♪♪

06:26.690 --> 06:28.605
I'll call you later.

06:28.692 --> 06:37.309
♪♪

06:37.397 --> 06:40.791
Dr. Gaetz: I heard you and Chuck
patched things up.

06:40.878 --> 06:42.184
[Door closes]

06:42.271 --> 06:45.535
Patched like a Band-Aid
on a bullet hole.

06:45.622 --> 06:49.191
Good for you.
No one stays together anymore.

06:49.278 --> 06:51.323
You bet.[Drawer closes]

06:51.411 --> 06:53.848
I know that thing with Tanya
seemed bad,

06:53.935 --> 06:58.679
but...you know,
I love my Miller Lite.

06:58.766 --> 07:01.116
But that doesn't mean
I'm not gonna sip from some Sam

07:01.203 --> 07:03.901
if there's an open bar.Buddy, there's a line.

07:03.988 --> 07:05.599
I am talking to --

07:05.686 --> 07:08.079
Yeah.
Excuse me.

07:08.166 --> 07:09.907
Uh, tell Chuck, um,

07:09.994 --> 07:12.867
he still owes me
for his bowling dues, okay?

07:12.954 --> 07:14.782
[Siren wailing in distance]

07:14.869 --> 07:16.479
[Door opens, bell chimes]

07:16.523 --> 07:17.785
Thank you.

07:17.872 --> 07:19.003
Guy's been my doctor
since I was 2.

07:19.090 --> 07:21.266
Even then,
I knew he was a dick.

07:21.353 --> 07:23.660
[Register beeping, clicking]

07:23.747 --> 07:25.749
Six-pack's $7.89.

07:25.836 --> 07:28.535
That's two dollars cheaper
than usual.

07:28.622 --> 07:32.147
I, um, I used my
employee discount for you.

07:32.234 --> 07:36.107
Just this once.
Don't get used to it.

07:36.194 --> 07:38.849
Well, shit.

07:38.936 --> 07:48.293
♪♪

07:48.380 --> 07:51.035
[Indistinct conversations,
down-tempo music playing]

07:51.079 --> 07:55.823
♪ Go out on the town and see
what's happening all around ♪

07:55.910 --> 07:58.434
Hi.

07:59.217 --> 08:00.741
Wow.

08:00.828 --> 08:04.527
Yeah. Well, not the worst answer
I was expecting.

08:04.571 --> 08:06.834
Well, I think it's generous,
considering.

08:06.877 --> 08:08.879
Y-Yeah.
No. I agree.

08:08.923 --> 08:12.056
But you just kind of walked away
the other night.

08:12.100 --> 08:14.319
You're not gonna tell anyone,
are you?

08:15.277 --> 08:17.235
I'm not gonna tell
anyone.

08:17.279 --> 08:20.021
I'm not sure anyone
would believe me anyways.

08:20.064 --> 08:21.675
Thank you.

08:21.718 --> 08:24.678
And thank you for putting me
in touch with the city hall guy.

08:24.721 --> 08:26.854
I, uh,
left him a message.

08:26.941 --> 08:29.509
He texted me, and he's gonna
get me what I need tonight.

08:29.596 --> 08:30.945
Yeah?
Yeah.

08:31.032 --> 08:34.122
I just need to find
$100 somewhere, but...

08:34.731 --> 08:35.819
No.

08:37.038 --> 08:38.343
No what?

08:38.430 --> 08:40.041
I'm not giving you
the money.

08:40.084 --> 08:41.216
I didn't ask for it.

08:41.259 --> 08:43.087
[Laughing] Okay.
No. I didn't.

08:43.174 --> 08:45.568
No, but you said it in that way
you always do,

08:45.655 --> 08:47.744
where I know what you need,
so I just give it to you.

08:47.788 --> 08:49.659
Okay, but that's not
what I'm getting at.

08:49.746 --> 08:50.921
That's just what you do.

08:51.008 --> 08:52.923
Yeah, and maybe that stuff
was worth it

08:53.010 --> 08:55.752
when I thought we might actually
be together.

08:55.839 --> 08:59.060
♪♪

08:59.147 --> 09:00.975
Wow.

09:01.062 --> 09:03.064
[Music stops]

09:03.107 --> 09:06.458
Uh...huh.

09:06.546 --> 09:10.941
♪♪

09:11.028 --> 09:13.074
Everything okay?

09:13.161 --> 09:14.510
Hmm?

09:14.597 --> 09:16.381
You look lost.

09:16.468 --> 09:19.384
Oh.
Uh...Um, no.

09:19.471 --> 09:20.777
I just...

09:20.821 --> 09:24.912
Um...would it be cool
if I kind of hung out

09:24.955 --> 09:26.566
and drank one of these
here?

09:26.653 --> 09:28.089
[Drawer closes]

09:28.176 --> 09:30.395
Technically
that's illegal.

09:31.571 --> 09:34.269
Right. Yeah.
S-Stupid.

09:35.139 --> 09:37.141
But I do it all the time.

09:37.185 --> 09:38.926
Knock yourself out.

09:40.275 --> 09:42.451
Thanks.

09:43.365 --> 09:46.934
Hey, um...
would you want one?

09:48.675 --> 09:51.068
[Chuckles]
Um...

09:51.155 --> 09:52.983
[Music stops]What...

09:53.070 --> 09:54.855
What'd you do?[Button clicking]

09:54.898 --> 09:56.813
I didn't do -- I just grabbed
a beer. I didn't do anything.

09:56.857 --> 09:58.815
[Mid-tempo music plays]

09:58.902 --> 10:06.693
♪♪

10:06.780 --> 10:14.614
♪♪

10:14.701 --> 10:16.616
[Cellphone chimes]

10:16.703 --> 10:24.493
♪♪

10:28.453 --> 10:31.326
Patty will be here soon,
so I'll be out of your hair.

10:31.369 --> 10:33.633
It's fine.

10:38.246 --> 10:40.030
You're still gonna meet up
with this guy?

10:40.117 --> 10:41.902
Yeah.

10:44.513 --> 10:45.819
Why?
Is he scary?

10:45.906 --> 10:47.908
I don't know.
I only texted with him.

10:47.995 --> 10:50.345
I got his number
from one of Jenn's uncles.

10:50.432 --> 10:51.738
I sent him money.

10:51.825 --> 10:53.261
He made my liquor license
happen.

10:53.348 --> 10:56.003
[Siren wailing in distance]

10:56.090 --> 10:57.831
Mm.

11:00.660 --> 11:04.489
You know, Allison...
you don't have to do this.

11:04.576 --> 11:07.536
Yeah, I know Kevin's a clown,
but...

11:07.623 --> 11:10.321
I'm not doing this
'cause my husband's a clown.

11:12.062 --> 11:14.586
You can get out of here.
I know how to lock up on my own.

11:14.630 --> 11:16.414
I already sent Maggie
and Jesse home.

11:16.501 --> 11:21.376
But, um, I'm gonna stick around,
just in case anyone wanders in

11:21.463 --> 11:23.770
and needs a place to wait
for the power to come back on.

11:23.857 --> 11:27.077
What kind of idiot wanders into
a dark restaurant in a blackout?

11:27.121 --> 11:29.166
[Door opens]Kevin: ♪ Who let the dogs in?!

11:29.210 --> 11:31.995
♪ Who, who, who, who, who! ♪
[Studio audience laughing]

11:32.082 --> 11:33.823
Why, why, why?

11:33.910 --> 11:35.651
Well, I tracked
your phone location,

11:35.738 --> 11:38.219
and I realized
that this empty diner

11:38.306 --> 11:40.569
is the perfect spot
to spend a blackout.

11:40.612 --> 11:42.702
Infinite food,
ample seating.

11:42.789 --> 11:45.922
And Lorraine to throw to
the angry hordes as a sacrifice.

11:46.009 --> 11:47.184
What?

11:47.271 --> 11:50.405
It's one of Kevin's
less funny bits!

11:50.448 --> 11:51.711
Lorraine lost her hearing aid,

11:51.798 --> 11:53.582
so today's been
a bit of a struggle.

11:53.669 --> 11:55.105
She did?
'Cause I found --

11:55.149 --> 11:56.890
Oh, no, no, no.
No -- No time.

11:56.977 --> 11:59.283
Uh, we've got to get
this dump

11:59.370 --> 12:02.199
turned into a luxury shelter
ASAP!

12:02.286 --> 12:05.507
Sammy, you got any screws
to hang a projector screen?

12:05.594 --> 12:08.379
I'm looking to fire up
my "Blue Bloods" DVDs.

12:08.466 --> 12:09.946
There's no electricity,
Kevin.

12:10.033 --> 12:11.818
Uh, correction, Sam.

12:11.861 --> 12:13.950
Theyhave no electricity -
the rest of Worcester --

12:13.994 --> 12:16.561
because theydon't have
Kevin's generator.

12:16.605 --> 12:18.041
We, on the other hand...

12:18.128 --> 12:20.087
♪ Ahh-h-h-h-h ♪ Ahh-h-h-h-h ♪

12:20.174 --> 12:21.305
You have a generator.Yeah.

12:21.349 --> 12:22.698
Well, it doesn't seem
like it,

12:22.785 --> 12:24.613
but Kevin is prepared
for any disaster.

12:24.700 --> 12:26.920
Otherwise, he'd die first.Pshh!

12:27.007 --> 12:28.835
Yeah.
I guess.

12:28.878 --> 12:30.401
[Studio audience laughing]
Yeah, right.

12:30.445 --> 12:32.142
Oh.
What are you doing here?

12:32.229 --> 12:33.578
Allison told me to come.

12:33.665 --> 12:35.755
She didn't say there'd be
other people here,

12:35.842 --> 12:37.931
even though she knows I hate
other people.

12:38.018 --> 12:41.412
Everyone, it is time to revel
in our electricity

12:41.499 --> 12:43.153
and superiority.

12:43.240 --> 12:45.634
All right. Now, where do you put
the batteries in this bad larry?

12:45.721 --> 12:47.592
[Sighs]Oh, no.

12:47.679 --> 12:48.593
The what?

12:48.680 --> 12:50.160
Yeah. What?

12:50.247 --> 12:51.683
I took all the 9-volts

12:51.771 --> 12:53.033
out of our smoke detectors
for this thing.

12:53.120 --> 12:55.992
It doesn't take batteries.
It takes gas.

12:56.036 --> 12:59.300
Like that riding mower you got
that chopped Neil's toe off.

12:59.387 --> 13:01.606
I apologized for that,
Patty.

13:01.693 --> 13:03.173
Yeah --
You said "Que sera"

13:03.217 --> 13:05.132
and threw his toe in my yard
somewhere.

13:05.219 --> 13:07.743
Please tell me
you found it.

13:07.787 --> 13:10.833
Uh...yeah.
[Studio audience laughing]

13:10.877 --> 13:13.705
Patty, let's go find
some fuel.

13:13.749 --> 13:17.187
Allison, be reasonable!
It's a blackout!

13:17.274 --> 13:19.059
I can't send
two helpless women

13:19.146 --> 13:21.801
out into the postapocalyptic
wild to die

13:21.888 --> 13:24.847
because I made the first mistake
of my life.

13:24.891 --> 13:27.241
Kevin, your father's a priest,
and your mother's a nun.

13:27.328 --> 13:28.546
Think about it.

13:28.590 --> 13:30.635
Your whole life
was based on a mistake.

13:30.722 --> 13:32.681
[Laughs]

13:32.768 --> 13:35.379
Oh -- All right.
I...

13:35.466 --> 13:36.903
Go look for gas, then!

13:36.990 --> 13:37.860
Okay.

13:37.947 --> 13:39.383
You're leaving me?Yeah.

13:39.427 --> 13:42.691
It'll be a blast.
Kevin's a real clown.

13:42.734 --> 13:45.302
It's true.

13:45.389 --> 13:46.913
Even my tears are funny.

13:46.956 --> 13:49.176
[Sobbing]
[Studio audience laughing]

13:49.263 --> 13:52.353
[Mid-tempo music plays]

13:56.139 --> 13:59.534
What are you doing?
Volunteering to help Kevin?

13:59.577 --> 14:00.927
No, I'm not.

14:01.014 --> 14:03.016
I'm getting
the death certificate.

14:03.103 --> 14:03.973
Tonight.

14:04.060 --> 14:05.845
Gertrude's.
Wait. How?

14:05.932 --> 14:08.543
Sam got me the number
of this shady guy at city hall,

14:08.630 --> 14:11.241
and he texted me back
saying that for 100 bucks,

14:11.328 --> 14:12.677
he could get me
the paper.

14:12.764 --> 14:16.377
So...we should go.

14:17.247 --> 14:18.553
Okay.

14:18.640 --> 14:20.207
W-- Really?

14:20.250 --> 14:22.252
Yeah.
Let's do it.

14:22.296 --> 14:23.906
I-I thought
you were gonna say

14:23.993 --> 14:26.387
that we should wait for
the electricity to come back on

14:26.474 --> 14:28.650
or for you to find
a Valium.

14:28.737 --> 14:30.957
Ah. I don't think
it'll be any less sketchy

14:31.044 --> 14:32.697
if we wait till the lights
are on.

14:32.784 --> 14:34.525
Besides,
I got to do something

14:34.612 --> 14:38.051
instead of sitting at home
in the dark, stuck in my head.

14:38.138 --> 14:39.487
What's wrong?

14:40.227 --> 14:41.576
Nothing.

14:41.663 --> 14:43.708
Nothing.
Let's go.

14:43.795 --> 14:45.449
Oh, shoot.

14:45.493 --> 14:47.060
I forgot to steal money
from Kevin.

14:47.147 --> 14:48.583
I don't have any cash
on me.

14:48.670 --> 14:51.412
We'll stop at the salon.
It's right there.

14:51.499 --> 14:52.369
Okay.

14:52.456 --> 14:54.589
Thanks.
Yeah.

14:54.676 --> 14:56.721
Nice haircut,
by the way.

14:56.808 --> 14:58.506
Thank you.

14:58.593 --> 15:01.378
[Grunts]
Sammy, my man.

15:01.465 --> 15:04.294
I'm gonna make some popcorn as
soon as we get this genny going.

15:04.381 --> 15:05.948
Question for you --

15:06.035 --> 15:08.995
Do you have any butter,
hopefully of the tub quantity?

15:09.082 --> 15:10.605
Yeah.
In back.

15:10.692 --> 15:12.215
Great!
But -- No!
Don't go in there!

15:12.302 --> 15:15.784
Don't stand between a man
and his butter, Sam!

15:15.827 --> 15:18.787
[Studio audience laughing]

15:18.874 --> 15:20.789
Whoa.

15:20.876 --> 15:22.269
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa.

15:22.312 --> 15:26.490
Sammy...
are you living here?

15:26.577 --> 15:28.057
No.

15:28.144 --> 15:31.147
Oh, Sam,
the mattress is imprinted

15:31.191 --> 15:33.410
with the outline
of your ripped bod.

15:33.497 --> 15:35.151
Thank you.

15:35.238 --> 15:37.762
But yeah, I've slept here
a little bit lately.

15:37.849 --> 15:39.634
Stuff at home.
Just a rough patch.

15:39.721 --> 15:42.289
Sammy, if you were having
relationship issues,

15:42.376 --> 15:43.855
you should have come
to me.

15:43.943 --> 15:46.641
I'm Mr. Marriag.
Just ask my wife.

15:46.728 --> 15:49.426
I would, but you tossed her
into a high-crime area

15:49.513 --> 15:50.645
during a blackout.

15:50.688 --> 15:53.126
Okay.
I'll do it.

15:53.213 --> 15:54.431
Do what?

15:54.475 --> 15:57.739
I'll take you on
and save your marriage.

15:57.826 --> 16:01.525
I'm gonna give you
a true storybook ending,

16:01.612 --> 16:04.137
just like
"Romeo and Juliet."

16:04.224 --> 16:07.009
That story doesn't end
the way you think it does.

16:07.096 --> 16:09.011
You correct your wife
like that?

16:09.055 --> 16:10.491
[Chuckles]

16:10.578 --> 16:11.709
Yes.

16:11.753 --> 16:14.321
And that's
lesson number one.

16:14.408 --> 16:16.062
That's not necessary,
really.

16:16.149 --> 16:19.282
Um, I'd actually appreciate it
if you kept this to yourself.

16:19.369 --> 16:20.501
Forget you saw anything.

16:20.588 --> 16:22.459
Yeah.
Loud and clear.

16:22.546 --> 16:23.939
[Imitates zipper closing]

16:24.026 --> 16:25.549
[Pops lips, clicks tongue]

16:25.636 --> 16:28.378
Whoa-ho!
Whoa!

16:28.422 --> 16:31.686
That was a very interesting
sex story

16:31.773 --> 16:34.210
you just told me
in there, Sam!

16:34.254 --> 16:36.691
And the fact that it happened
just last night

16:36.778 --> 16:38.214
with your very own wife?

16:38.301 --> 16:41.043
Whoo!
That makes it even sexier.

16:41.087 --> 16:43.176
[Chuckles]

16:43.219 --> 16:47.354
Wait.
Something is...off.

16:47.441 --> 16:49.225
All the lights, son.

16:49.269 --> 16:50.618
[Studio audience laughing]

16:50.705 --> 16:52.185
Where's my generator?!

16:52.272 --> 16:53.969
It was right here.

16:54.013 --> 16:55.536
I know where it was,Ne!
Where is it now?

16:55.623 --> 16:57.625
Well, it couldn't have just
walked out of here.

16:57.712 --> 17:00.062
Uh, Sam...
[Chuckles]

17:00.149 --> 17:02.108
...marriage lesson
number two --

17:02.151 --> 17:05.720
Don't say stuff
that's insultingly obvious.

17:05.807 --> 17:11.595
Now...if Sam's very astute
observation is correct

17:11.682 --> 17:14.772
and it didn't just walk
out of here on its own,

17:14.816 --> 17:18.428
then that means that...
one of you stole it.

17:18.472 --> 17:20.126
Not me.What are you
talking about?

17:20.213 --> 17:21.344
What?!

17:21.388 --> 17:23.390
[Studio audience laughing]

17:28.699 --> 17:30.875
[Hinges squeaking,
keys jingling]

17:30.962 --> 17:32.399
It's dark in here.

17:32.486 --> 17:35.271
Well, it's a blackout.

17:35.315 --> 17:38.274
Okay.
You said you needed $100?

17:38.318 --> 17:40.233
Uh, just $71.

17:41.190 --> 17:43.627
Thank you
for being honest.

17:43.714 --> 17:44.933
Here.

17:45.020 --> 17:47.544
This is easier
than breaking into Cindy's.

17:47.631 --> 17:49.068
It's nice to have a door.

17:49.155 --> 17:50.982
Well, Allison,
we're not breaking in.

17:51.070 --> 17:52.767
I own the salon.

17:52.854 --> 17:55.422
[Exhales deeply]
The illegal shit happens next.

17:55.509 --> 17:57.772
Hey, someone's just handing us
a piece of paper.

17:57.859 --> 18:00.296
We're not knocking over
a liquor store, so don't worry.

18:00.383 --> 18:01.254
Okay.

18:01.341 --> 18:04.605
Okay.
Here -- $71.

18:07.347 --> 18:09.305
Do you not believe me?Sorry.

18:09.349 --> 18:11.046
I've had some trust issues
with money

18:11.133 --> 18:14.397
on account of, you know,
my marriage.

18:15.311 --> 18:16.878
I'm glad to hear it,
actually.

18:16.965 --> 18:19.054
Okay.
Now for the illegal shit.

18:19.141 --> 18:21.230
Okay.
[Knock on door]

18:21.317 --> 18:22.884
Man:
Police. Open up.

18:22.971 --> 18:24.668
[Dramatic music plays]

18:24.712 --> 18:26.844
Should I worry now?

18:26.931 --> 18:28.977
♪♪

18:34.417 --> 18:36.854
Hey, Patty![Exhales deeply]

18:36.941 --> 18:38.639
Sorry.
Didn't know it was you.

18:38.726 --> 18:41.032
Bye!Allison: Cops don't wave.
Why are they waving?

18:41.076 --> 18:42.773
They were at a party
at your house last week.

18:42.860 --> 18:45.254
Oh, God. They're gonna tell
Tammy they saw us.

18:45.341 --> 18:47.604
Is that bad?
Well...

18:47.648 --> 18:49.345
Unlock the door!

18:49.432 --> 18:50.738
Well, it's very obvious
that we're talking about them,

18:50.825 --> 18:52.870
so why don't you go --
go answer the door?

18:52.957 --> 18:54.611
Door.

18:54.698 --> 18:56.613
[Siren wailing, latch clicks]

18:56.657 --> 18:59.616
[Bell chimes]

18:59.703 --> 19:01.009
Hey, Patty.
Ah!

19:01.052 --> 19:02.445
H-Hi.Hi, Officers.

19:02.532 --> 19:03.968
So nice
to see you again.

19:04.055 --> 19:05.187
Right back at youse.

19:05.231 --> 19:06.319
We spotted the flashlight,

19:06.406 --> 19:07.494
thought it was looters,
you know?

19:07.581 --> 19:09.060
Parker:
What were you two doing here?

19:09.104 --> 19:11.019
Well, this is my salon,
and...
Uh-huh.

19:11.062 --> 19:13.326
Yes. And we were just getting,
uh, Patty's purse...

19:13.413 --> 19:15.415
Yes. Thank you....and, uh,
we were gonna leave.

19:15.502 --> 19:17.286
Moreno: We can give you a ride
to the house.

19:17.373 --> 19:19.810
Earn us a few extra points
with one Ms. Ridgeway.

19:19.897 --> 19:21.334
Uh...
We're, uh...

19:21.377 --> 19:23.031
We're just -- We're going
to our friend's house.

19:23.118 --> 19:25.512
Mm-hmm.
Gonna just kind of
hunker down there.

19:25.555 --> 19:27.035
Shelter in place.Shelter in place.

19:27.122 --> 19:28.950
Patty: Yeah.
On foot?

19:29.037 --> 19:30.299
Uh-huh.
Yes. Yep.

19:30.386 --> 19:32.562
'Cause she does live
quite close by.

19:32.606 --> 19:35.217
Great.
Then we can drive you.

19:35.261 --> 19:36.827
No.

19:36.871 --> 19:39.352
We just don't want to disturb
you while you're on duty.

19:39.395 --> 19:41.310
Ladies, stop trying to act
so brave.

19:41.397 --> 19:43.704
Let us give you a ride
to the goddamn house.

19:43.791 --> 19:47.664
♪♪

19:47.751 --> 19:50.450
In no time at all,
I've transformed

19:50.537 --> 19:52.930
Sam's depressing
office apartment

19:52.974 --> 19:55.063
into a makeshift...
interview room!

19:55.106 --> 19:56.934
[Studio audience laughing]

19:57.021 --> 19:58.327
Sam lives here?

19:58.414 --> 19:59.807
[Chuckles]
Totally.

19:59.894 --> 20:01.722
Pretty hot goss, huh?

20:01.809 --> 20:03.550
Come on, man.
You told people?

20:03.637 --> 20:04.942
No. No, no, no.
No, no.

20:05.029 --> 20:07.597
But it'd be some
pretty hot goss, right?

20:07.641 --> 20:10.644
Look, I obviously know
it wasn't you,

20:10.731 --> 20:12.646
but I know you're protecting
Diane.

20:12.733 --> 20:15.649
Why would I protect Diane?
Diane hates me.

20:15.736 --> 20:17.216
You're clearly protecting
Pete.

20:17.303 --> 20:20.219
Why would I protect Pete?
I hate Pete.

20:20.306 --> 20:21.872
You shouldn't have accepted
that doughnut.

20:21.959 --> 20:25.267
Now I've got your prints.[Muffled] Prints for what?

20:25.311 --> 20:28.096
[Studio audience laughing]

20:28.139 --> 20:32.796
You claim to have seen nothing,
but did you hearanything?

20:32.883 --> 20:33.928
What?

20:34.015 --> 20:35.059
A generator thief
says what?

20:35.146 --> 20:36.713
"A generator thief
says what?"

20:36.757 --> 20:38.411
A generator thief
says what?

20:38.498 --> 20:39.760
Huh?

20:39.847 --> 20:40.978
A generator thief
says what?

20:41.022 --> 20:42.284
Sorry.
I can't hear you.

20:42.328 --> 20:44.460
[Studio audience laughing]

20:44.504 --> 20:46.419
[Mid-tempo music plays]

20:46.506 --> 20:49.160
[Vehicles passing,
indistinct talking on radio]

20:49.204 --> 20:52.163
Moreno: Tammy's a changed woman
since you came around, Pat.

20:52.207 --> 20:54.775
Always swore she'd never date
another neighborhood gal --

20:54.818 --> 20:56.255
or a smoker.

20:56.342 --> 20:58.213
Yeah. You got her breakg
all the rules.

20:58.300 --> 21:00.171
Yeah, and I swore
I'd never talk to a cop

21:00.259 --> 21:02.173
without a lawyer present,
but here we are.

21:02.261 --> 21:04.132
[Laughs]

21:04.698 --> 21:06.265
Hey, we should all give her
a call together.

21:06.352 --> 21:08.441
Yeah, I think -- I think she
would get a kick out of that.

21:08.528 --> 21:09.746
No.

21:09.833 --> 21:11.052
Thank you.

21:12.488 --> 21:14.577
[Exhales deeply]

21:15.317 --> 21:18.538
[Mid-tempo music plays]

21:18.625 --> 21:20.148
Jesus, it's hot.

21:20.235 --> 21:21.758
You look like Diane
getting a hot flash.

21:21.845 --> 21:23.456
You okay?[Groans]

21:23.543 --> 21:25.153
♪♪

21:25.196 --> 21:28.199
Patty?
Stop being so weird.

21:28.287 --> 21:29.679
Just act normal.

21:29.766 --> 21:31.028
We're -- We're in a car
with your friends.

21:31.115 --> 21:33.466
You think we could roll
the window down?

21:33.553 --> 21:35.424
In February?

21:36.686 --> 21:37.861
[Weakly]
Yeah.

21:37.948 --> 21:39.646
Uh, she's -- she --
She gets carsick.

21:39.733 --> 21:41.256
She's --
She's getting carsick.

21:41.343 --> 21:42.475
[Groans softly]

21:42.518 --> 21:44.346
Parker:
Lovely article this morning.

21:44.390 --> 21:45.652
What?

21:45.739 --> 21:47.262
The profile
in the paper?

21:47.349 --> 21:49.264
I didn't know Kevin's wife
was such a phenom.

21:49.351 --> 21:52.006
Ah.
Or that you worked
at Defto's.

21:52.049 --> 21:54.051
[Groaning]

21:54.138 --> 21:55.662
Oh!

21:55.749 --> 21:58.317
Uh, there's our friend's house,
just on the corner.

21:58.404 --> 21:59.927
We can get out here.

22:00.014 --> 22:01.189
Yeah.What?
It's -- That's half a block.

22:01.276 --> 22:02.843
No, we'll take you
all the way there.

22:02.930 --> 22:04.671
No, that's okay.
Thank you.

22:04.714 --> 22:06.194
Thank you.

22:06.281 --> 22:07.456
Go.
Thank you.

22:07.543 --> 22:08.544
Oh --
Go.

22:08.631 --> 22:12.374
♪♪

22:12.461 --> 22:15.159
Allison, you got to get me
out of this thing.

22:15.246 --> 22:16.900
Oh. My seat belt's stuck.
Hold on.

22:16.944 --> 22:18.380
I don't care
about the seat belt.

22:18.424 --> 22:19.816
I'm gonna throw up.

22:19.903 --> 22:21.035
Stop.
Get out of the car.

22:21.122 --> 22:22.993
Out of the car.
Okay. Okay.

22:23.080 --> 22:24.299
Bye.
Thank you.

22:24.386 --> 22:25.909
Quickly.

22:25.953 --> 22:27.737
Bye.
[Dog barking]

22:27.824 --> 22:28.912
Have a good one.

22:28.999 --> 22:30.523
You too.
Yeah.

22:32.307 --> 22:34.657
What is wrong with you?

22:36.920 --> 22:38.705
I got hot.

22:38.792 --> 22:40.228
You freaked out.

22:40.271 --> 22:42.578
I know.
[Exhales deeply]

22:42.622 --> 22:45.233
But who is this guy?
You know?

22:45.320 --> 22:48.541
He's willing to break the law
for 100 bucks.

22:50.238 --> 22:51.979
And Tammy knows
those guys.

22:52.066 --> 22:53.894
Is something going on
with you two?

22:53.981 --> 22:55.809
Kind of.
[Exhales deeply]

22:55.896 --> 22:57.680
Let's just get the cops
to leave.

22:57.767 --> 23:00.030
Yeah. Thank you.
The house is here.

23:00.117 --> 23:01.162
Thank you.
Yeah.

23:01.249 --> 23:02.772
Moreno:
You're welcome, ladies!

23:02.859 --> 23:04.252
Why aren't they leaving?

23:04.339 --> 23:07.386
Because God hates me.

23:07.821 --> 23:08.952
[Clears throat]

23:09.039 --> 23:10.519
Well, whoever
this guy is,

23:10.606 --> 23:13.000
I hope he at least looks
respectable.

23:13.087 --> 23:15.263
[Metal squeaks]

23:15.959 --> 23:17.439
Over here.

23:17.483 --> 23:18.919
Ow.

23:20.050 --> 23:22.488
[Hinges squeaking]

23:25.316 --> 23:26.753
Oh.
I am so sorry.

23:26.796 --> 23:28.972
I think we must have
the wrong house.

23:29.059 --> 23:31.279
Oh, you must be Alice.

23:31.366 --> 23:32.411
Yes.

23:32.498 --> 23:33.629
That's her.

23:33.673 --> 23:35.283
So glad you made it.

23:35.370 --> 23:37.459
Uh, quick question, dear,
before you come in --

23:37.546 --> 23:40.767
What are those goddamn pigs
doing parked on my street?

23:40.854 --> 23:42.551
Huh?

23:42.638 --> 23:45.162
[Down-tempo music plays]

23:45.249 --> 23:49.297
♪♪

23:53.257 --> 23:57.305
Yeah, 35 years of my life I gave
to those city hall pricks.

23:57.348 --> 23:59.133
My best years.
[Chuckles]

23:59.220 --> 24:01.570
But I believed
in civic duty!

24:01.657 --> 24:03.529
And back then,
you think it was some picnic

24:03.616 --> 24:05.139
being the only woman
at that place?

24:05.226 --> 24:07.620
Unh-unh.No. No.

24:07.707 --> 24:08.925
Yeah. That's right.

24:09.012 --> 24:12.538
Geez. Oh, then I get
"let go" -- by e-mail!

24:12.625 --> 24:17.151
So, uh, yeah, I guess civic duty
is a one-way street.

24:17.238 --> 24:18.979
Could have taken that place
down, too.

24:19.066 --> 24:20.981
The stuff I saw.

24:21.068 --> 24:22.548
Mm.
[Exhales deeply]
Yeah.

24:22.635 --> 24:25.333
Well, I am -- I am so sorry
that happened to you.

24:25.376 --> 24:27.204
Yeah, so now
whenever I get a call

24:27.248 --> 24:29.468
from someone looking for
a liquor license

24:29.555 --> 24:32.253
or some mousy delinquent
and her goth friend

24:32.340 --> 24:33.559
looking for
a death certificate,

24:33.646 --> 24:35.996
I'm like,
"Hey, show me the money!"

24:36.083 --> 24:37.998
Goth?Thank you.

24:38.085 --> 24:39.652
I changed my hair.
Ah! Bingo!

24:39.739 --> 24:40.827
Here it is.

24:40.914 --> 24:42.785
Okay. [Grunts]
Oh, boy.

24:42.872 --> 24:45.135
Slow.[Metal jingling]

24:45.222 --> 24:46.615
What is this?

24:46.702 --> 24:48.095
Keys.

24:48.182 --> 24:50.053
Uh, no.
I-I know.

24:50.097 --> 24:51.533
I know they're keys,
but why --

24:51.620 --> 24:53.230
Where's the
death certificate?

24:53.317 --> 24:55.581
Oh, the records room
is on the third floor,

24:55.668 --> 24:57.060
through the clerk's office.

24:57.147 --> 24:58.409
And here.

24:58.453 --> 25:01.804
Take these flashlights.
And good luck.

25:01.891 --> 25:03.545
Good luck?

25:03.632 --> 25:05.199
Yeah.
Power's out.

25:05.286 --> 25:07.331
No one's there.
[Chuckles]

25:07.418 --> 25:09.377
This is kismet.What does that mean?

25:09.464 --> 25:11.597
And I cannot vouch
for the condition for the place,

25:11.640 --> 25:14.861
'cause after I left, they hired
someone's delinquent nephew

25:14.948 --> 25:16.558
to take over, so...

25:16.602 --> 25:18.691
So you want us
to break into city hall?

25:20.214 --> 25:21.737
I'm not doing it.

25:21.824 --> 25:23.043
♪♪

25:23.130 --> 25:24.479
Right.

25:24.566 --> 25:26.786
Right.

25:28.439 --> 25:30.224
Thank you.

25:30.311 --> 25:32.879
Are we really gonna break io
a government building?

25:32.966 --> 25:34.881
You heard her.
She said it's the perfect time.

25:34.968 --> 25:37.666
Shouldn't we stop
and talk about this?

25:37.753 --> 25:40.930
Where's that
ever gotten us?
Oh.

25:40.974 --> 25:42.932
[Dog barking in distance]

25:42.976 --> 25:45.195
Sam, let's get down
to brass tacks.

25:45.282 --> 25:46.675
Why am I a suspect?

25:46.762 --> 25:49.112
I was in here with you
when the generator was stolen.

25:49.199 --> 25:50.766
You're not a suspect.

25:50.853 --> 25:53.552
This is time for us to work on
marriage lesson number 16.

25:53.595 --> 25:55.554
Can I be a suspect
instead?

25:55.641 --> 25:59.209
Now, Sam, what do you know
about funniness?

25:59.296 --> 26:00.994
What?Geez.

26:01.081 --> 26:03.736
You sound like Lorraine ever
since I stole her hearing aid.

26:03.823 --> 26:05.302
You did?
That's awful.

26:05.346 --> 26:08.305
No, no, Sam.
Thatis funny.

26:08.392 --> 26:11.265
And funniness is
my greatest strength.

26:11.352 --> 26:12.788
Well, that
and my muscles --

26:12.875 --> 26:16.009
and everything else,
including my brain.

26:16.096 --> 26:19.273
So you think I need to be funny
to get my wife to like me again?

26:19.360 --> 26:20.840
Oh, absolutely not.

26:20.927 --> 26:23.320
You're too hot
to have a sense of humor.

26:23.407 --> 26:27.803
Me, on the other hand, I am the
rare exception that has both.

26:27.847 --> 26:30.850
You need to find yourthing
and use it --

26:30.893 --> 26:34.331
you know, your strength
that makes you so lovable,

26:34.375 --> 26:36.290
you can get away
with whatever you want.

26:36.377 --> 26:37.900
I don't have that.

26:37.987 --> 26:39.989
Come on!
Don't sell yourself short.

26:40.033 --> 26:42.688
Play up that, uh,
sensitive thing you got going.

26:42.731 --> 26:45.386
You know, tell her --
tell her that you're broken.

26:45.473 --> 26:48.171
Tell her that you guys can fix
each other.

26:48.258 --> 26:49.608
Tell her you're in AA.

26:49.695 --> 26:50.826
I'm in AA.

26:50.913 --> 26:52.175
Score!

26:52.219 --> 26:54.961
[Studio audience laughing]

26:55.048 --> 26:57.398
[Siren wailing in distance]

26:58.181 --> 27:00.270
Allison:
Hey. Here we go.Patty: Yep, yep.

27:00.357 --> 27:02.229
We're doing this.

27:03.273 --> 27:04.753
We're doing this?

27:04.840 --> 27:06.799
Well, we got the ke.
The power's out.

27:06.886 --> 27:09.192
It's kismet, right?
I guess.

27:09.236 --> 27:10.454
I'm still not sure.

27:10.498 --> 27:11.804
It'll be easy.

27:11.891 --> 27:13.719
It makes me so nervous
when you do that.

27:13.806 --> 27:15.024
Do what?

27:15.111 --> 27:16.896
Think things are easy
when they're not.

27:16.983 --> 27:18.637
It'd just make me feel better
if you'd admit

27:18.724 --> 27:20.334
this might not be
the best idea.

27:20.421 --> 27:23.119
Well, that just feels like
negative thinking.

27:23.206 --> 27:24.599
[Latch clicks]
Ah!

27:24.686 --> 27:26.732
[Down-tempo music plays]

27:26.819 --> 27:30.126
♪♪

27:30.213 --> 27:32.563
[Hinges squeaking]

27:32.651 --> 27:34.522
♪♪

27:34.609 --> 27:36.176
Wait!

27:37.612 --> 27:40.093
An alarm needs electricity.
This thing's dead.

27:40.180 --> 27:41.572
It's city hall.

27:41.660 --> 27:43.357
They probably have some
crazy advanced backup system

27:43.444 --> 27:46.142
for stuff like this.Patty, this is
Worcester City Hall.

27:46.229 --> 27:47.361
Look at this thing.
Don't --

27:47.448 --> 27:49.711
[Clanging, clattering]Oh!

27:49.755 --> 27:52.018
See? Easy.

27:52.975 --> 27:54.890
Simple.
Mm.

27:54.977 --> 27:59.373
♪♪

27:59.460 --> 28:03.594
Well, after some
amateur detective work

28:03.638 --> 28:06.336
that I'm sure
even Scruff McGruff himself

28:06.423 --> 28:07.903
would be proud of,

28:07.947 --> 28:11.211
I've correctly deduced
who the thief if.

28:11.298 --> 28:13.387
All right. Which one of these
losers was it, Kev?

28:13.474 --> 28:17.173
Well, Neil, I'd say
it's the biggest loser of all.

28:17.217 --> 28:20.220
Because you stole
the generator!
[Studio audience laughing]

28:20.307 --> 28:23.702
And you've lost weight recently.
Congrats.

28:23.789 --> 28:26.052
What?
You can't be serious.

28:26.139 --> 28:28.489
I'm as serious
as Dad's coronary event,

28:28.576 --> 28:31.927
which they're now classifying
as "inevitable."

28:32.014 --> 28:33.015
What?

28:33.102 --> 28:36.105
I have nothing
to leave you.

28:36.192 --> 28:38.020
You've been sabotaging me
all day.

28:38.107 --> 28:40.022
You bailed
on fireworks practice,

28:40.109 --> 28:42.111
which is why I shot 'em
too low,

28:42.155 --> 28:43.591
which is how I blew up

28:43.678 --> 28:46.594
that giant electrical
transformer this afternoon.

28:46.681 --> 28:49.510
Wait. So it's your fault
the power is out?

28:49.597 --> 28:51.730
No.
It's Neil's fault!

28:51.773 --> 28:52.818
Gosh.
Weren't you listening?

28:52.905 --> 28:54.776
No.
I was listening.

28:54.863 --> 28:56.560
You really believe, aftr
everything we've been through,

28:56.647 --> 28:57.910
I'd steal from you?

28:57.997 --> 29:00.956
Not only do I believe it,
I know it to be true!

29:01.043 --> 29:05.918
In fact, this case is wide open
and slammed shut.

29:05.961 --> 29:07.789
Just like the car door,

29:07.876 --> 29:11.097
which I caught Dad's hand in
earlier today.

29:11.184 --> 29:13.577
Did I apologize
for that yet?

29:13.664 --> 29:16.363
You said "Que sera."

29:16.450 --> 29:19.061
I don't even know
what it means.

29:19.105 --> 29:21.281
[Studio audience laughing]

29:28.244 --> 29:30.594
[Grunts]

29:35.425 --> 29:38.646
Hey.
Are you okay?

29:40.039 --> 29:42.693
[Down-tempo music plays]

29:42.781 --> 29:49.352
♪♪

29:49.439 --> 29:56.838
♪♪

29:56.882 --> 29:57.796
Whoa.

29:57.883 --> 30:02.322
Yeah.
It's very...official.

30:02.365 --> 30:04.803
You ever been here
before?

30:04.846 --> 30:07.501
Whenever Neil has
his court dates.

30:07.544 --> 30:09.503
Wow.

30:09.590 --> 30:11.853
So weird that Worcester
City Hall is so nice

30:11.940 --> 30:15.683
and the rest of the town's...
Worcester.

30:16.989 --> 30:19.426
It's not all bad.

30:21.471 --> 30:22.516
[Hinges squeaking]

30:22.559 --> 30:24.518
Oh.
How you feeling?

30:24.605 --> 30:27.521
Like maybe I should've
kept things off my mind tonight

30:27.564 --> 30:29.001
by reading a nice book.

30:29.088 --> 30:32.439
My friend Judi gave me
"The Secret Life of Bees."

30:32.526 --> 30:34.006
Okay.
Okay.

30:34.093 --> 30:35.616
[Clears throat]

30:35.703 --> 30:37.313
[Latch clicks]Pull!

30:37.400 --> 30:39.054
[Hinges squeaking]

30:39.098 --> 30:41.187
You did it.

30:41.230 --> 30:43.058
Oh.

30:43.102 --> 30:45.234
[Mid-tempo music plays]

30:45.321 --> 30:47.541
♪♪

30:47.628 --> 30:50.718
I hate it
when I'm right.

30:58.769 --> 31:00.162
I'm not finding it.

31:00.249 --> 31:02.121
Well, it's got to be
in here.

31:02.208 --> 31:03.687
We had a small change
of plans,

31:03.774 --> 31:06.212
but sometimes you just got to
roll with it, right?

31:06.255 --> 31:07.561
Well, we didn't have
a plan.

31:07.648 --> 31:09.345
Don't you think --
No, no. No.

31:09.432 --> 31:11.086
Because when I think too h
about something,

31:11.173 --> 31:14.350
that's the second I start
talking myself out of it, okay?

31:14.437 --> 31:15.874
That's not true.

31:15.961 --> 31:19.181
Well, maybe not for you,
but it is for me.

31:20.356 --> 31:23.882
You've known me for 15 years.
Have I ever done anything?

31:24.795 --> 31:26.406
You --
No.

31:26.493 --> 31:29.409
I can't even blame Kevin for it,
'cause it's always been true.

31:29.496 --> 31:32.586
I make excuses, and I bail,
and I make excuses, and I bail,

31:32.673 --> 31:34.980
and, "Allison, you just always
make excuses and bail!"

31:35.067 --> 31:36.895
[Drawer slams]Jesus.

31:36.938 --> 31:39.245
[Down-tempo music plays]

31:39.288 --> 31:41.116
I'm sorry.

31:41.203 --> 31:42.770
Ah.

31:42.857 --> 31:44.903
I just need to fid
this thing tonight,

31:44.946 --> 31:46.817
and I can't let
a little trespassing

31:46.861 --> 31:50.256
or some shitty nephew
who can't alphabetize

31:50.299 --> 31:52.258
create any more excuses.
Okay.

31:53.215 --> 31:55.130
Okay.

31:55.217 --> 31:57.132
Okay, but you must know --[Gasps]

31:57.219 --> 31:58.481
What?

31:58.568 --> 32:01.789
Gertrude Fronch.
[Snorts]

32:01.876 --> 32:04.661
It is a terrible name,
but I found it.

32:04.748 --> 32:06.098
Ha!

32:06.185 --> 32:09.579
♪♪

32:09.623 --> 32:10.841
[Door closes]

32:10.929 --> 32:12.278
Hang on.
Wait.

32:12.365 --> 32:13.540
W-- Really?

32:13.627 --> 32:15.585
You don't actually believe
any of that?

32:15.672 --> 32:16.978
That's bullshit.

32:17.022 --> 32:18.806
You are not
some hopeless screw-up.

32:18.893 --> 32:20.677
Okay.
No.

32:20.764 --> 32:22.027
Don't do that.

32:22.114 --> 32:23.811
♪♪

32:23.854 --> 32:25.987
I'm here.

32:26.074 --> 32:29.208
I've been here,
standing next to you.

32:30.600 --> 32:32.515
If you're some loser
who can't do anything,

32:32.559 --> 32:38.130
I follow your lead...
what does that make me?

32:38.217 --> 32:40.915
♪♪

32:41.002 --> 32:42.830
[Thud, alarm blaring]

32:42.873 --> 32:44.745
I guess you are right
sometimes.

32:44.832 --> 32:47.661
[Alarm blaring]

32:51.752 --> 32:53.058
What?

32:53.101 --> 32:54.189
[Studio audience laughi]

32:54.276 --> 32:56.800
Kevin, you caused
a citywide power outage,

32:56.887 --> 32:58.193
raided my diner,

32:58.237 --> 33:00.369
and basically held everyone
in here hostage.

33:00.456 --> 33:01.849
I think you owe us
an apology.

33:01.892 --> 33:05.374
Yeah.
We're...upset.

33:05.418 --> 33:07.115
[Studio audience laughing]

33:07.202 --> 33:10.640
And you should say you're...
sorry?

33:12.860 --> 33:15.863
Apologies are like tears.

33:15.906 --> 33:20.563
Everyone has to let them out
unless they're a real man.

33:20.650 --> 33:22.348
Dad, you taught me that!

33:22.435 --> 33:23.740
I-I never said that.

33:23.827 --> 33:25.090
What?

33:25.177 --> 33:26.743
How come I can't get through
to you today?

33:26.787 --> 33:29.224
Because Kevin stole
her hearing aid.

33:29.311 --> 33:30.486
What?!
What?!

33:30.573 --> 33:32.053
Okay.
Hold on.

33:32.097 --> 33:35.578
In my defense....
it has been pretty funny.

33:35.665 --> 33:37.015
[Laughs]

33:37.102 --> 33:39.321
And did you do this
before or after you caused

33:39.408 --> 33:42.977
a citywide emergency
where hearing would be crucial?

33:43.064 --> 33:44.718
Oh, way before.

33:44.761 --> 33:47.242
You have to take responsibility
for something,Kevin.

33:47.286 --> 33:48.417
Anything.

33:48.461 --> 33:50.637
Oh, Neil,
I'm so glad that you're back

33:50.724 --> 33:52.465
from your little...
crying thing.

33:52.552 --> 33:54.554
Will you please remind
these fine people

33:54.641 --> 33:57.383
of some of
my good qualities?

33:57.426 --> 33:58.775
I got nothing.

33:58.862 --> 34:01.648
See, Neil kn--
Wait. What?

34:01.735 --> 34:03.911
I guess you're pretty good
at accusing people

34:03.954 --> 34:05.739
of stealing
your dumb generator.

34:05.826 --> 34:07.828
Yeah.
And causing blackouts.

34:07.871 --> 34:11.875
Yeah. I'm starting to think that
maybe I should cause a blackout.

34:11.962 --> 34:13.181
Kill him!

34:13.268 --> 34:14.095
What?

34:14.182 --> 34:16.532
Uh, I--
Hit him!

34:16.619 --> 34:19.318
[Down-tempo music plays]

34:19.970 --> 34:23.931
The lights --
They're back on!

34:23.974 --> 34:26.238
[Studio audience laughing]

34:26.325 --> 34:27.413
Hey, look!

34:27.500 --> 34:31.286
[Chuckles]
Well, will you look at that?

34:31.330 --> 34:33.941
Everyone was all mad
at me,

34:34.028 --> 34:36.291
and the generator
wasn't even missing!

34:36.335 --> 34:38.989
It was right here,
under this table!

34:39.077 --> 34:42.210
Oh, I bet you all feel
real stupid now.

34:42.297 --> 34:44.038
But how did it get
over there?

34:44.125 --> 34:46.345
It's on wheels, D.
It must have just rolled.

34:46.388 --> 34:49.217
Sam, you're probably gonna
want to level out this floor.

34:49.304 --> 34:50.479
That's a real hazard.

34:50.523 --> 34:52.090
You'rea hazard.

34:52.177 --> 34:53.917
Ha!
That's the spirit.

34:54.004 --> 34:55.571
All right, gang.

34:55.658 --> 34:57.486
What do you say we have
some more laughs about this

34:57.573 --> 34:59.314
over a few dozen beers,
yeah?

34:59.401 --> 35:00.620
You go ahead.

35:00.707 --> 35:03.666
I'll catch up as soon
as I level out my floor.

35:03.753 --> 35:06.321
Don't worry, hon.
We'll get you a new hearing aid.

35:06.408 --> 35:07.627
What?

35:07.714 --> 35:09.803
It's a good thing
you're so good at sex.

35:09.846 --> 35:11.848
[Chuckles]
Damn right I am.

35:11.892 --> 35:13.415
[Studio audience laughing]

35:13.502 --> 35:16.766
[Down-tempo music playing]That was intense.

35:17.202 --> 35:19.421
Blackouts do that.

35:19.508 --> 35:21.336
People go nuts.

35:21.380 --> 35:23.338
People do.

35:23.382 --> 35:26.646
That explains all that stuff...
outside.

35:27.690 --> 35:29.475
Probably related
to the whole blackout thing.

35:29.518 --> 35:31.868
Huh. Yeah. Totally.
Sure.

35:31.912 --> 35:34.480
Yeah. I mean, it has to be
a blackout thing.

35:34.523 --> 35:36.656
Chuck still has
his sawed-off, so...

35:36.743 --> 35:39.833
Right.
Of course.

35:39.876 --> 35:41.965
So...

35:42.052 --> 35:45.708
You hid the generator,
right?

35:45.795 --> 35:47.319
What?

35:47.406 --> 35:49.190
Come on.

35:49.277 --> 35:50.844
Pete would never.

35:50.887 --> 35:52.976
I don't even think Lorraine knew
there was a generator.

35:53.063 --> 35:55.196
And I didn't do it,
so...

35:55.283 --> 35:57.024
♪ I found you... ♪

35:57.067 --> 35:59.505
Are you smarter
than Kevin?

35:59.592 --> 36:01.594
Not if you ask Kevin.

36:02.899 --> 36:05.293
Huh.

36:05.380 --> 36:07.295
Yeah. Okay.
I did.

36:08.340 --> 36:09.863
Think of it as payback
on Kevin

36:09.906 --> 36:12.170
for trying to set me up
with Pete.

36:12.257 --> 36:14.955
Hmm.

36:15.042 --> 36:16.391
♪ You know that's true ♪

36:16.435 --> 36:19.351
So, what are you gonna do,
rat on me?

36:19.438 --> 36:21.309
♪ I found my someone... ♪

36:21.396 --> 36:25.400
I'm gonna...
I'm gonna go to Dunkin'.

36:25.487 --> 36:29.404
♪ ...the day I found you You want anything?

36:29.448 --> 36:32.146
Sure,
if you wouldn't mind.

36:32.233 --> 36:33.669
Light and extra sweet.

36:33.756 --> 36:35.193
Oh.
Oh, n--

36:35.280 --> 36:38.892
No, I'm not gonna, like,
get it for you.

36:38.979 --> 36:41.982
I was asking
if you want to come.

36:42.069 --> 36:45.725
♪ Lonely days have passed ♪

36:45.768 --> 36:47.117
Whatever.

36:47.205 --> 36:48.293
Fine.

36:48.380 --> 36:49.250
Fine.

36:49.294 --> 36:54.342
♪ I'm glad I found you

36:54.429 --> 36:57.954
♪ At last ♪

36:58.041 --> 37:04.091
It's weird wanting something
so bad and finally getting it.

37:04.178 --> 37:06.136
It's new.

37:06.224 --> 37:07.442
Yeah.

37:07.529 --> 37:09.749
[Dog barking, horn blowing
in distance]

37:09.836 --> 37:12.317
I'm moving in with Tammy.

37:12.404 --> 37:14.710
You are?

37:14.797 --> 37:17.757
Yeah. She'd been acting
really weird recently.

37:17.800 --> 37:21.151
So I went over there thinking
she was gonna break up with me,

37:21.239 --> 37:23.545
but she just asked me
to move in.

37:25.068 --> 37:26.983
And you said yes?

37:27.070 --> 37:28.681
No.

37:30.248 --> 37:32.380
But I'm gonna.

37:32.467 --> 37:35.427
[Down-tempo music plays]

37:35.514 --> 37:39.431
You won't live here
anymore.

37:39.518 --> 37:44.262
♪♪

37:44.349 --> 37:46.916
Neither will you.

37:47.003 --> 37:53.793
♪♪

37:53.836 --> 37:54.968
Hey.

37:58.711 --> 38:00.452
I'm happy for you.

38:00.539 --> 38:03.455
[Exhales sharply]

38:03.542 --> 38:05.457
Good night, Gertrude.

38:06.240 --> 38:08.024
Night, Patty.

38:08.111 --> 38:13.943
♪♪

38:13.987 --> 38:15.336
[Door closes]

38:15.380 --> 38:17.643
[Cellphone ringing]

38:21.299 --> 38:22.778
Hello?

38:26.521 --> 38:29.307
Hey.
Thanks for coming by.

38:29.394 --> 38:30.133
Hey.

38:30.220 --> 38:31.961
[Exhales deeply]
Yeah.

38:32.048 --> 38:33.311
Yeah. Okay.
Yeah.

38:33.398 --> 38:35.138
Tonight was terrible.

38:35.225 --> 38:38.664
I was so annoyed
with Kevin.

38:38.751 --> 38:42.537
No, not annoyed.
I was, uh, disgusted.

38:42.624 --> 38:43.799
Yeah.
Yeah.

38:43.886 --> 38:46.715
He kept giving me
terrible marriage advice.

38:46.802 --> 38:49.152
Like...awful things.

38:49.239 --> 38:52.460
But I-I think...

38:52.547 --> 38:54.767
I think I do a lot of it,
and...

38:54.854 --> 38:58.858
I don't know that I'm actually
that much better than him.

39:01.339 --> 39:02.992
[Clears throat]

39:03.079 --> 39:04.864
You should have
your job back.

39:06.213 --> 39:09.042
It was wrong,
the way I fired you.

39:09.869 --> 39:14.526
I made it about me,
and -- and...I'm really sorry.

39:14.569 --> 39:16.963
[Down-tempo music plays]

39:17.790 --> 39:20.140
I do want to help you.

39:26.276 --> 39:28.540
[Exhales sharply]
Um, I'm sorry.

39:28.627 --> 39:30.019
I'm sorry.

39:30.106 --> 39:30.977
That's okay.
No.

39:31.064 --> 39:32.805
I'm -- I am so sorry.

39:32.892 --> 39:34.633
It's okay.
I'm so sorry.

39:34.720 --> 39:36.591
[Sobs]

39:36.635 --> 39:38.593
Oh. Oh.

39:38.680 --> 39:40.421
♪♪

39:40.508 --> 39:41.727
Okay.

39:41.770 --> 39:43.685
[Sobbing]

39:43.772 --> 39:46.079
It's okay.
It's okay.

39:46.122 --> 39:47.646
It's okay.

39:51.954 --> 39:53.391
So you're still mulling
how you're going to

39:53.478 --> 39:55.697
fake your own death?

39:55.784 --> 39:57.264
Like I said,
I haven't...

39:57.351 --> 39:58.570
figured it out yet.

39:58.657 --> 40:00.180
Allie,
you're stalling.

40:00.267 --> 40:01.877
You haven't packed yet?

40:01.964 --> 40:03.357
I shouldn't read into this,
right?

40:03.444 --> 40:04.880
Absolutely not.

40:06.012 --> 40:07.274
Oh...

40:07.361 --> 40:08.536
[Laughing]

40:08.623 --> 40:10.059
This is the last thing
I need to do.

40:10.146 --> 40:11.365
The last thing.

40:11.452 --> 40:12.975
One...
Uh-huh.

40:13.062 --> 40:14.803
Two...

40:14.890 --> 40:16.979
Man: Allison.Yeah?

40:17.066 --> 40:20.418
♪♪

40:21.549 --> 40:23.986
[Down-tempo music plays]

40:24.073 --> 40:32.342
♪♪

40:32.430 --> 40:40.655
♪♪

40:40.742 --> 40:49.229
♪♪
